  "A small island has 3 sectors: fishing, farming, and tourism. The consumption matrix has column sums 0.6, 0.7, and 0.5. A planner increases tourism demand by $10 million. Using the Leontief model, total production must increase. Which sector's production is directly computed by the model?": "",
