  "A company produces chairs (c) and tables (t). Each chair requires 2 hours of carpentry and 1 hour of finishing. Each table requires 3 hours of carpentry and 2 hours of finishing. Available: 120 hours of carpentry and 70 hours of finishing. The system is 2c + 3t = 120 and c + 2t = 70. How many tables can be produced?": "",
  "From eq 2: c = 70 - 2t. Substitute into eq 1: 2(70-2t) + 3t = 120, 140 - 4t + 3t = 120, -t = -20, t = 20. Then c = 70 - 40 = 30.": "",
  "A bank offers two investment products. A client invests a total of $100,000 split between Product X (earning 5%) and Product Y (earning 8%). She wants total annual interest of $6,500. How much should she invest in Product X?": "",
